1047.description: Jahan Dotson's first career NFL touchdown was an impressive one, as he made a leaping catch before getting two feet down inbounds with the back of the end zone looming. But his second touchdown was even more stunning, as he pulled in a highly contested pass in the end zone with under two minutes to play to give the Commanders the lead and, ultimately, the win. Dotson caught three passes for 40 yards and two touchdowns in the game, a 28-22 victory over the Jaguars on Sept. 11, 2022.

1153.description: Malcolm Rodriguez was all over the field for Detroit against Miami. First, he pulled quarterback Tua Tagovailoa down for a sack. Then, in a heads-up play, he tracked the ball and recovered a fumble to give possession back to the Lions' offense. He finished with seven total tackles, including a sack, in the game, a 31-27 Detroit loss to the Dolphins on Oct. 30, 2022.

435.description: Trevor Lawrence eyed Laquon Treadwell down the right side of the field and let this long pass fly. With safety help coming over the top, Treadwell made a nice adjustment to meet the ball and reel it in for a gain of 41 yards. He finished with four catches for 68 yards in the Jaguars' 20-0 loss to Tennessee on Dec. 12, 2021.

446.description: Completion No. 7,143 of Tom Brady's career, a newly minted NFL record, had to be a memorable one, right? As the blitz closed in on third down, Brady lofted this pass toward the left sideline where Mike Evans swooped in and made the catch for a first down inside Buffalo's five-yard line. With the completion, Brady passed Drew Brees for No. 1 on the league's all-time list. He finished the game 31-of-46 for 363 yards and two touchdowns in a 33-27 win over Buffalo on Dec. 12, 2021.

468.description: Leonard Floyd was keeping an eye on quarterback Kyler Murray, who tried to float this one over his head and to the intended target on the far sideline. But the ball never arrived, tipped and intercepted by Floyd and returned down inside the 10-yard line. He added eight total tackles on the night in the Rams' 30-23 win over Arizona on Dec. 13, 2021.

680.description: Andy Dalton eyed Damien Williams leaking out of the backfield and, with coverage late to pick him up, floated this pass down the near sideline for the score. Dalton finished 33-of-48 for 325 yards with one touchdown and two interceptions in Chicago's 31-17 loss to Minnesota on Jan. 9, 2022.

1104.description: Nick Bolton had an unimpeded path to the quarterback and took advantage, pulling Matt Ryan down for the sack just outside of the red zone. The takedown halted the Indianapolis drive and held the Colts to a field goal. Bolton registered nine tackles, including two sacks, in the game, a 20-17 loss to Indianapolis on Sept. 25, 2022.

368.description: Down by eight points in the fourth quarter, Minnesota needed a touchdown, and K.J. Osborn delivered this diving gem in the back of the end zone. He caught four passes for 47 yards, though it came in a 29-27 loss to Detroit on Dec. 5, 2021.

364.description: Ben Skowronek found space in the middle of the Jacksonville defense and quarterback Matthew Stafford dropped it to him for a 35-yard gain into Jacksonville territory. This was Skowronek's lone catch of the day in a 37-7 Los Angeles win over the Jaguars on Dec. 5, 2021.

752.description: No one picked up Tershawn Wharton as he came bursting through the line, giving him an unimpeded run at the quarterback. He wrapped up Ben Roethlisberger, brought him down for the third-down sack, and forced a Pittsburgh punt. It was Wharton's lone tackle -- but an impactful one -- in Kansas City's 42-21 win over the Steelers on Jan. 16, 2022.

627.description: On 4th and 2 and trailing by four points from just outside the 10-yard line, the Raiders needed Derek Carr to make a play. He did. Rolling to his right to escape pressure, Carr threaded the needle to find wide receiver Hunter Renfrow for the score. Carr finished 24-of-31 on the day for 255 yards with one touchdown and two interceptions in Las Vegas' 23-20 win over Indianapolis on Jan. 2, 2022.

1116.description: Alexander Mattison was split out wide when he caught this screen pass in the red zone. He did the rest, making use of a block and making another would-be tackler miss en route to a 15-yard touchdown. It was Mattison's lone reception of the game in a 28-25 Vikings win over New Orleans in London on Oct. 2, 2022.

1222.description: Latavius Murray took this pitch to the left and danced his way towards the end zone, extending towards the goal line as he got hit to reach across for the crucial fourth-quarter score. Murray had a sensational day, totaling 130 rushing yards to go with his touchdown in the Broncos' 24-15 win over Arizona on Dec. 18, 2022.

724.description: A.J. Green posted up in the middle of the Seattle defense and took in this Kyler Murray pass, but it was an impressive juke move that made a defender miss that allowed him to turn up the field and into Seahawks territory. Green caught four passes for 23 yards in Arizona's 38-30 loss to Seattle on Jan. 9, 2022.

716.description: Green Bay was looking to tie the game with under 0:30 to play and a seven-point deficit. Tracy Walker III put an end to their comeback hopes here, intercepting this overthrown pass to seal Detroit's 37-30 victory on Jan. 9, 2022. Walker III added 14 tackles in the win.

390.description: Down by two scores, Cincinnati looked poised to get at least one of those back with just over eight minutes to play in the game. Chris Harris Jr. had other ideas, picking off this Joe Burrow pass in the end zone to stop the Bengals' drive in its tracks. Harris Jr. added four tackles on the day in a 41-22 Chargers win on Dec. 5, 2021.

831.description: Javon Walker worked his way behind the defense as his quarterback rolled out off the play action on this play, tracking the ball and pulling it in for the 54-yard score. Walker caught five passes on the day for 84 yards and this touchdown in a 37-20 Broncos win over Arizona on Dec. 17, 2006.

922.description: Marquise Brown got behind two Cincinnati defenders on this play and quarterback Lamar Jackson spotted him, lofting this deep pass down the near sideline. It was an impressive play in tight space from there, with Brown dragging two feet inbounds to complete the catch for a 39-yard score. He finished with five catches for 80 yards and this touchdown in the game, a 41-17 loss to Cincinnati on Oct. 24, 2021.

1238.description: Phillip Dorsett showed off the skills that made him a 2015 first-round pick on this play. Stretching the field on a fade route, Dorsett found himself needing to contort his body at the last second to turn back towards the sideline in order to make the grab. The 34-yard gain was his longest on the day, and he finished with three catches for 69 yards in the Texans 29-17 loss to Philadelphia on Nov. 3, 2022.

1097.description: Chris Olave's first career NFL touchdown came in a tight spot in the red zone, with the rookie juking toward the pylon before breaking back inside and pulling this pass in at the goal line before the defender could arrive. The four-yard score was part of a four-catch, 67-yard day for Olave. The Saints would fall to Minnesota in London, 28-25, on Oct. 2, 2022.

1090.description: Rookie Kyle Hamilton helped Baltimore protect its slim fourth-quarter lead on this play, chasing down wide receiver Nelson Agholor and stripping the ball from behind. It bounced into the arms of teammate Marcus Peters for the recovery, giving the ball back to the Baltimore offense. Hamilton added three total tackles in the game, a 37-26 victory over New England on Sept. 25, 2022.

514.description: With Nick Bosa in pursuit, quarterback Matt Ryan stepped up to try to avoid the pressure, but couldn't escape. Bosa corralled him from behind and stripped the ball, forcing a turnover and giving the ball back to the 49ers' offense. It was Bosa's lone tackle of the game, but a hugely important one, in a 31-13 San Francisco win over Atlanta on Dec. 19, 2021.

469.description: Lurking behind the intended receiver, Landon Collins took advantage when this ball was overthrown, grabbing the interception and giving the ball back to the Washington offense. Collins had two sacks and five total tackles to go along with this pick in Washington's 27-20 loss to Dallas on Dec. 12, 2021.

691.description: Matched up on a corner, tight end Tyler Higbee used his size to his advantage on this impressive touchdown catch, rising up above the defender and pulling it in for the score with little room available to him along the sideline. Higbee caught six passes on the day for 55 yards and two touchdowns in the Rams' 27-24 loss to San Francisco on Jan. 9, 2022.

832.description: Terrell Davis found a hole on the left side and darted through it, getting to the second level of the Jacksonville defense and pushing into the red zone. He dodged one diving defender and took a hit from another, which propelled him into the end zone on this 37-yard touchdown run. Davis carried the ball 31 times for 136 yards and three touchdowns on the day in Denver's 37-24 win over the Jaguars on Oct. 25, 1998.

356.description: How's this for a first career touchdown? Brock Wright found space down the seam, made the catch, and absorbed the hit to reel in the score. It was one of two catches for him on the day in Detroit's 29-27 victory over Minnesota on Dec. 5, 2021.

886.description: Justin Herbert dropped back, then saw a lot of open space in front of him, so he took it himself, picking up 36 yards and setting the Chargers up in the red zone. Herbert carried the ball nine times for 90 yards in the game, along with completing 30-of-41 passes for 382 yards and three touchdowns in a 41-37 Los Angeles win over Pittsburgh on Nov. 21, 2021.

889.description: Kenneth Gainwell saw daylight up the middle and ran to it, darting through the line virtually untouched for this touchdown. He carried the ball nine times for 37 yards in the game, including this score, and helped the Eagles to a 32-6 win over Atlanta on Sept. 12, 2021.

1092.description: Jacoby Brissett got Cleveland's first points of the game on the board by taking it himself, escaping up the middle and freezing a defender with a nifty pump fake before breaking toward the far pylon and diving in for the touchdown. Brissett finished 21-of-35 for 234 passing yards and carried the ball five times for 16 yards, including this touchdown, in the game, a 23-20 loss to Atlanta on Oct. 2, 2022.

842.description: One defender dodged. A second. A stiff arm around the outside. Dive for the end zone. Touchdown. Shaun Alexander had to work hard for this six-yard touchdown, but he got there to extend Seattle's lead in the second quarter. Alexander carried the ball 28 times for 135 yards and two touchdowns on the ground in the game. He added another through the air and Seattle would go on to win, 21-7, on Sept. 12, 2004.

825.description: Working in single coverage, Odell Beckham Jr. shaded toward the pylon on the near side of the field and quarterback Matthew Stafford put it where only OBJ could get it, allowing the receiver to go up and make the grab for the first touchdown of the game. Beckham made a big impact early, catching two passes for 52 yards and this score in the game before exiting with an injury. His team pulled together in his absence to win Super Bowl LVI over Cincinnati, 23-20, on Feb. 13, 2022.

812.description: Kyle Pitts burst off the line of scrimmage near the goal line and broke toward the far sideline, creating separation from his defender. That was enough of a window for Matt Ryan to find him with this pass for Pitts' first career NFL touchdown. Pitts caught nine passes for 119 yards and the score on the day in Atlanta's 27-20 win over the Jets in London on Oct. 10, 2021.

1041.description: An impressive spin move freed Micah Parsons en route to the quarterback, collapsing the pocket and giving him a free path to the quarterback for a third-down sack. The takedown halted Tampa Bay's drive and helped the Dallas defense hold the Buccaneers to just a field goal. Parsons tallied five total tackles in the game, including two sacks, in Dallas' 19-3 loss to Tampa Bay on Sept. 11, 2022.

375.description: With Atlanta trailing by just three points and driving to tie or take the lead early in the third, Pierre Desir delivered a big play. Poking the ball out from behind, he got the ball back for the Tampa Bay offense. The Buccaneers would go on to win, 30-17, on Dec. 5, 2021.

820.description: Jessie Bates III shadowed Van Jefferson as quarterback Matthew Stafford directed the wide receiver to the back of the end zone and let this pass fly. Bates high-pointed the ball and pulled it in for the interception, ending the Rams' drive with close to two minutes to go before halftime of Super Bowl LVI. He added six total tackles in the game, though Cincinnati would ultimately fall, 23-20, on Feb. 13, 2022.

804.description: Quickness. Power. Speed. Balance. Deebo Samuel used just about every tool in his toolbox to make his way through the Rams' defense en route to a 44-yard touchdown here. He caught four passes for 72 yards and carried the ball seven times for 26 yards, though the 49ers would fall to Los Angeles in the NFC Championship Game, 20-17, on Jan. 30, 2022.

805.description: George Kittle found a soft spot in the Los Angeles defense and Jimmy Garoppolo found him, lofting this pass up high for Kittle to go grab and bring in for the score. The touchdown and extra point gave San Francisco a 10-point lead late in the third quarter, though they were unable to maintain that lead in a 20-17 loss to Los Angeles in the NFC Championship Game on Jan. 30, 2022. Garoppolo finished 16-of-30 for 232 yards with two touchdowns and one interception in the loss.

655.description: Patrick Mahomes II makes no-look, sidearm passes look easy. He did that here, escaping pressure and holding the defender in place with his eyes while he found Blake Bell coming across the field for the completion and a gain of 24 yards. Mahomes finished 26-of-35 for 259 yards and two touchdowns in the Chiefs' 34-31 loss to Cincinnati on Jan. 2, 2022.

353.description: One hand was all Olamide Zaccheaus needed to make this tough grab in the red zone late in the fourth quarter for Atlanta. Adjusting with the defender in front of him, he was able to pull it in as the Falcons continued their late push before ultimately running out of time in a 30-17 loss to Tampa Bay on Dec. 5, 2021.

1081.description: Deebo Samuel appeared to be cornered in the backfield on this run, but one juke shook a would-be tackler and he darted through another hole to pick up a first down and much more. In all, the 51-yard gain moved San Francisco into Seattle territory on a drive that would end in a field goal. Samuel carried the ball four times for 53 yards and caught five passes for 44 yards in the game, a 27-7 win over Seattle on Sept. 18, 2022.

1306.description: Kellen Winslow came up big when it mattered most, catching two touchdown passes in the fourth quarter of the AFC Wild Card Round matchup between the Chargers and Steelers to turn an 11-point deficit into a 31-28 San Diego lead. That scoreline would hold, with Winslow's seven-catch, 102-yard, two-touchdown performance fueling the Chargers' victory on Jan. 9, 1983.

492.description: Devin Singletary took the handoff out of the shotgun here and found a hole, then cut it up field, absorbed two hits, and tumbled into the end zone for the 16-yard touchdown. He carried the ball 22 times for 86 yards and this score on the day in a 31-14 Bills win over the Panthers on Dec. 19, 2021.

843.description: Derrick Brooks took on a would-be blocker and pushed past him as he broke down the pocket, swatting at the ball as he moved past the quarterback and causing a fumble. Tampa Bay would recover and capitalize on the turnover by adding a field goal before halftime. Brooks tallied 11 total tackles, including two sacks, in the game and helped the Buccaneers to a 27-0 shutout win over Atlanta on Dec. 5, 2004.

747.description: After picking up the first down, Devin Singletary bounced it outside and picked up a block. It was a race to the end zone from there, which he won, scampering in from 16 yards out for a touchdown to extend Buffalo's lead before halftime. Singletary carried the ball 16 times on the day for 81 yards and two touchdowns in the Bills' 47-17 victory over New England on Jan. 15, 2022.

692.description: The pocket collapsed, so Tua Tagovailoa took off, juking past one would-be tackler and breaking into open space. He crossed midfield and got a block to spring him forward for a 23-yard gain and a Miami first down. Tagovailoa finished 15-of-22 for 109 yards and a touchdown to go along with five carries for 38 yards in the Dolphins' 33-24 victory over New England on Jan. 9, 2022.

619.description: The play action from Baker Mayfield freed up Harrison Bryant in the end zone, where Mayfield found him on this fourth-quarter touchdown. Mayfield was 16-of-38 for 185 yards with two touchdowns and two interceptions in Cleveland's 26-14 loss to Pittsburgh on Jan. 3, 2022.

431.description: Albert Okwuegbunam would not be denied on this catch and run. Making the grab but with traffic ahead of him, he fought forward to brush aside one would-be tackler, absorb a hit from another, and lunge forward for the score. He caught five passes for 41 yards and this score in a 38-10 win over Detroit on Dec. 12, 2021.

1243.description: Connor Heyward was wide open down the middle of the field and quarterback Kenny Pickett found him, with some nifty footwork by Heyward in the back of the endzone ensuring he completed the catch on this 17-yard score. It was Heyward's lone catch of the game, part of a 19-17 Steelers win over Atlanta on Dec. 4, 2022.

838.description: Daunte Culpepper glanced right before locking in on his target to the left, launching this deep ball to Troy Williamson, who had gotten a step on his defender down the far sideline. Williamson pulled it in and fell forward into the end zone, giving the Vikings six points on the 53-yard connection. Culpepper finished 21-of-29 for 300 yards and three touchdowns in a 33-16 Minnesota win over New Orleans on Sept. 25, 2005.

727.description: DK Metcalf found open space in the Arizona defense and Russell Wilson found him with this floating pass down into the red zone for a first down. The Seahawks would score four plays later to take the lead in the second quarter. Metcalf caught five passes for 58 yards on the day in a 38-30 Seattle win over Arizona on Jan. 9, 2022.

1114.description: Rookie Jelani Woods was the hero for Indianapolis in a clutch Week 3 performance. He caught two passes and both were touchdowns, one to open the scoring in the first quarter and one to give the Colts the lead -- and ultimately the win -- in the fourth quarter. That would give Indianapolis its first victory of the season, 20-17, over Kansas City on Sept. 25, 2022.

923.description: The Rams got creative on this play, putting a receiver in motion, then faking a handoff to the running back before quarterback Matthew Stafford pitched it to receiver Robert Woods on the reverse. Woods got to the edge and turned up the field, weaving between a pair of blocks for the 16-yard score. Woods carried the ball three times for 22 yards and caught three passes for 35 yards, registering two total touchdowns in the game, a 38-22 win over Houston on Oct. 31, 2021.

984.description: Incompletion. Stuffed the run. Incompletion. Goal-line stop. The Eagles stood up the Chargers and held them without points after Los Angeles had driven 98 yards to the doorstep of the end zone, keeping the game scoreless. Philadelphia would ultimately fall on a last-second field goal, 27-24, on Nov. 7, 2021.

628.description: Zay Jones broke toward the near sideline on this deep route and found space in the Indianapolis defense, pulling in this nicely floated pass from Derek Carr to move the Raiders into Colts territory for a gain of 42 yards. Las Vegas would score four plays later to take the lead and would go on to win, 23-20, on Jan. 2, 2022. Jones finished with eight receptions for 120 yards in the victory.

970.description: Mike Gesicki only needed one hand to pull in this Jacoby Brissett pass over the middle, tucked into a soft spot in the Houston defense. He caught four passes for 54 yards in the game, a 17-9 Miami win over the Texans on Nov. 7, 2021.

612.description: On third down, Antoine Wesley was able to get separation from the defender at the line before leaping and twisting at the goal line to high-point this pass from Kyler Murray and bring it in for the score. On the day, Wesley caught four passes for 30 yards and two touchdowns in a 25-22 Arizona win over Dallas on Jan. 2, 2022.

969.description: Trevor Lawrence eyed his tight end down the seam and found him with this pass, leading him to the end zone for six. It was Lawrence's first career NFL touchdown pass, part of a 28-of-51 day for the rookie where he threw for 332 yards with three touchdowns and three interceptions. The Jaguars would fall to the Texans, 37-21, on Sept. 12, 2021.

851.description: Tracking the ball the whole way, Herman Moore adjusted to come back to the ball as this pass was in the air, shaking his defender and pulling it in for the catch. A nifty spin and extension of the ball got him into the end zone for the 29-yard score. Moore caught six passes on the day for 147 yards and three touchdowns in a 24-16 win over Green Bay on Oct. 29, 1995.

534.description: Brandon Aiyuk pulled in this pass off a slant route and went to work. Dipping and dodging through the Atlanta defense, he picked up the first down and headed into Falcons territory to keep the 49ers moving down the field. This was Aiyuk's lone catch of the game for 36 yards in a 31-13 San Francisco win over Atlanta on Dec. 19, 2021.

723.description: T.J. Watt made history on this play, tying the league's single-season sack record with sack No. 22.5 after pulling down Tyler Huntley just before halftime. Coming off the edge, he shuffled away from one block and dipped by another on his way to the quarterback. Watt had five total tackles in the game, a 16-13 win over Baltimore on Jan. 9, 2022.

948.description: Tyler Lockett worked his way across the formation before reversing course and shaking two defenders in the process. Quarterback Russell Wilson saw him and floated this pass toward the near sideline. Lockett pulled it in in stride and turned up the field for a gain of 48 yards and a Seahawks first down. He caught four passes for 115 yards in the game, a 23-13 Seattle loss to Arizona on Nov. 21, 2021.

393.description: When Vita Vea broke through the line, he was locked in on the quarterback. In one swift motion, he pulled Matt Ryan to the ground, one of his two sacks on the day in a 30-17 win over the Falcons on Dec. 5, 2021.

1100.description: Rashaad Penny was the engine for Seattle's offense in a game where they nearly posted 50 points against Detroit. He carried the ball 17 times for 151 yards, including touchdown runs of 41 yards and 36 yards. His impressive effort powered the Seahawks to a 48-45 road win over the Lions on Oct. 2, 2022.

774.description: Fourth down. Four yards to go. Under three minutes to play. Josh Allen kept Buffalo's hopes alive with this dipping, dodging scramble toward the near sideline that picked up just enough for the first down. The Bills would score a touchdown on the drive to take the lead, part of a wild back-and-forth final stretch in regulation before the game went to overtime. Buffalo would ultimately fall in the extra session, 42-36, but Allen put on a masterful performance. He finished 27-of-37 passing for 329 yards with four touchdowns and no interceptions through the air, to go along with 11 carries for 68 yards on the ground in the Jan. 23, 2022 defeat.

466.description: Baltimore was looking to drive and take the lead with close to a minute to play in the fourth quarter, but Jadeveon Clowney wanted to do his part to put an end to that. Coming around the edge, the pass rusher took down a scrambling Tyler Huntley for the sack. He had 1.5 sacks on the day and three total tackles in a 24-22 Cleveland win on Dec. 12, 2021.

1309.description: Torry Holt opened this NFC Wild Card matchup in style, first finding space deep down the field to get open for a 52-yard reception to set the Rams up in the red zone, then finishing off the drive a few plays later with a 15-yard TD reception to put the game's first points on the board. Holt tallied six catches and 108 receiving yards on the day, including that touchdown, as the Rams pulled off the hard-fought 27-20 victory over Seattle on Jan. 8, 2005.

813.description: The Dolphins got creative with Jaylen Waddle here, bringing him in motion before the snap only to have him reverse course and track quarterback Tua Tagovailoa as he rolled out to the left on play action. Blockers sealed the edge as Waddle pulled in the short pass, giving him a lane to the end zone. One broken tackle and a dive got him across the goal line for his first career NFL touchdown. He caught four passes for 61 yards and this score in the game, a 17-16 Miami victory over New England on Sept. 12, 2021.

1026.description: Damien Harris took this pitch and turned it upfield, crossing the 50-yard line and looking for more. He kept his legs moving as he made contact with a would-be tackler, powering through to pick up extra yardage. It was one of Harris' 10 carries in the game for 56 yards, part of a 25-0 New England win over Atlanta on Nov. 18, 2021.

1161.description: Kayvon Thibodeaux's game-sealing strip sack showed why he was a top-five pick in the 2022 NFL Draft. As quarterback Lamar Jackson tried to escape pressure, Thibodeaux swiped at the football, sending it bouncing on the turf and into the arms of teammate Leonard Williams. The Giants would run the clock out from there to secure a 24-20 win over the Ravens on Oct. 16, 2022. Thibodeaux tallied three total tackles in the game.

360.description: Logan Cooke dropped this punt about as close as it can get to the goal line without being a touchback. Some nice footwork by Daniel Thomas kept it out, and the Jaguars downed it inside the 1-yard line. Cooke punted five times on the day for an average of 49.4 yards in Jacksonville's 37-7 loss to Los Angeles on Dec. 5, 2021.

1298.description: Anquan Boldin opened the scoring in Super Bowl XLVII with this leaping grab towards the back of the end zone that he hauled in and hung onto as he tumbled to the ground. Boldin's big six-catch, 104-yard performance played a huge role in Baltimore ultimately pulling out the tight 34-31 victory over the 49ers on Feb. 3, 2013.

1154.description: Sebastian Joseph-Day kept his eyes in the backfield on this play, shedding a would-be blocker and meeting running back Kenneth Walker III behind the line to take him down, along with teammate Troy Reeder, for the safety. Joseph-Day tallied four total tackles in the game, a 37-23 Chargers loss to the Seahawks on Oct. 23, 2022.

1046.description: Contorting his body while pulling the ball in with one hand in the end zone? Mike Evans made it look easier than it should be. It was one of five catches on the day for Evans for 71 yards and a touchdown, part of a 19-3 Tampa Bay win over Dallas on Sept. 11, 2022.

982.description: New York had driven down inside the Carolina five-yard line with under two minutes to play in the first quarter, looking to take the lead. The Panthers had other ideas. Carolina's defense stopped the Giants four times to force the turnover on downs, punctuated by a goal-line stuff of running back Devontae Booker. Carolina would fall, though, 25-3, on Oct. 24, 2021.

835.description: Marvin Harrison's stop-and-go hesitation on this route was enough to pull the safety toward him, which freed him to go deep and pull in this 68-yard pass for the score. Harrison caught seven passes for 172 yards and this touchdown in the game, a 20-17 loss to Tennessee on Dec. 3, 2006.

1291.description: Chase Claypool can make contested catches with the best of them. On this play, Claypool fought through the contact along the sideline and utilized his helmet to make the difficult grab on a rainy day in New York. The Bears' new playmaking wideout finished with two catches for 51 yards on the day, a 31-10 Chicago loss to the Jets on Nov. 27, 2022.

560.description: With just over two minutes to play, Detroit needed a big play and Jalen Reeves-Maybin delivered. He forced this fumble and set Detroit up with a new set of downs, already in Atlanta territory. Reeves-Maybin had eight total tackles in the game. After regaining possession, The Lions were unable to ultimately take advantage as a red zone interception ended their comeback hopes. They would fall to Atlanta, 20-16, on Dec. 26, 2021.

985.description: Rhamondre Stevenson was on a mission after taking this pitch, dipping past would-be Titans tacklers and taking on another defender before picking up a fresh set of downs after a gain of 19 yards. Stevenson carried the ball nine times for 46 yards in the game, a 36-13 victory over Tennessee on Nov. 28, 2021.

850.description: Rookie Reggie White was impressive in his first NFL game, registering 2.5 sacks -- including this, the first takedown of his career -- against the Giants. He would go on to tally 13 sacks during his rookie season, the start of a Hall of Fame career. The Eagles would fall to the Giants, 16-10, on Sept. 29, 1985.

563.description: As a free rusher barrelled toward quarterback Carson Wentz, he had to get the ball out quickly. That's when Nyheim Hines did his part on the far sideline, making a full extension to reel this one in for a catch. It was his lone catch of the day for seven yards and he carried the ball three times for 11 yards in Indianapolis' 22-16 win over Arizona on Dec. 25, 2021.

760.description: No one picked up Rob Gronkowski after this play action, leaving him wide open in the middle of the end zone from two yards out. Tom Brady found him with the easy pass and Tampa Bay extended its lead in the third quarter. Gronkowski caught five passes for 31 yards and this score on the day in a 31-15 Buccaneers win over Philadelphia on Jan. 16, 2022.

442.description: Split out wide to the right, Saquon Barkley's fake to the inside had the defender trying to jump the route. When Barkley broke back up the field, he found himself wide open in the end zone for the score. Barkley caught three passes for 31 yards and carried the ball 16 times for 64 yards on the day in a 37-21 loss to the Chargers on Dec. 12, 2021.

557.description: Ja'Marr Chase can beat the defense deep, sure. But here he showed the work he can do in the middle of the field, pulling in this pass from Joe Burrow and juking one defender and then another to bounce it to the edge and pick up more yardage to push into the red zone on this 22-yard gain. Chase caught seven passes for 125 yards in Cincinnati's 41-21 win on Dec. 26, 2021.

966.description: With under two minutes to play in the first half, the Cardinals wasted no time. Kyler Murray eluded the rush, rolled toward the near sideline, and then spotted Rondale Moore wide open down the field. He let it fly, Moore pulled it in and did the rest, taking it 77 yards for the touchdown. Moore caught seven passes for 114 yards and this score in the game, a 34-33 win over Minnesota on Sept. 19, 2021.

1237.description: Penei Sewell, TE1? The Lions' star offensive tackle lined up off the line on the left before going into motion and drifting out right, where quarterback Jared Goff found him wide open. Sewell made the catch and converted the crucial fourth-quarter third down, which led to a Lions field goal that finished off their 34-23 win over Minnesota on Dec. 11, 2022.

533.description: Jacksonville brought the pressure on third down and Davis Mills adjusted, floating this ball to Phillip Dorsett II in single coverage for the first down and more into the red zone. Mills finished 19-of-30 for 209 yards, two touchdowns, and one interception in Houston's 30-16 win over the Jaguars on Dec. 19, 2021.

786.description: Tom Brady didn't see Von Miller as he burst around the edge, who then swiped down and forced a fumble on this strip sack. He recovered it himself, as well, giving the ball back to the Los Angeles offense with a readymade possession in Tampa Bay territory. Miller tallied four total tackles in the Rams' 30-27 win over the Buccaneers on Jan. 23, 2022.

695.description: Darius Slayton was wide open in the end zone here, leaping to pull in this touchdown grab to give New York its first points of the game. It was one of two catches for Slayton on the day in the Giants' 22-7 loss to Washington on Jan. 9, 2022.

773.description: Jerick McKinnon did a little bit of everything to impact Kansas City's playoff win over Pittsburgh, carrying the ball 12 times for 61 yards while also catching six passes for 81 yards and a touchdown. His all-around game helped lift the Chiefs to a 42-21 victory on Jan. 16, 2022.

759.description: Elijah Mitchell made good use of a block from Kyle Juszczyk on the right side to cut back inside and race to the pylon for the touchdown. The play capped a seven-play, 75-yard drive and gave San Francisco its first points of the game. Mitchell carried the ball 27 times for 96 yards on the day in the 49ers' 23-17 victory over Dallas on Jan. 16, 2022.

701.description: Antonio Gibson cut it back, broke a tackle, and added a little bit of flare at the end of this 18-yard touchdown run. He carried the ball 21 times for 146 yards and this score on the day, a 22-7 victory over New York on Jan. 9, 2022.

1111.description: Kansas City got creative on this goal-line play, with tight end Noah Gray coming under center as quarterback Patrick Mahomes II created a diversion by pointing to the left side of the formation. The ball was snapped to Gray, who pushed forward for the one-yard touchdown. It was Gray's lone carry in the game, a 41-31 Chiefs victory over Tampa Bay on Oct. 2, 2022.

656.description: Elijah Mitchell was able to shed a tackle as he cut this one up the field, which turned a short gain into a 37-yard burst, down inside the Houston 10-yard line. Mitchell carried the ball 21 times for 119 yards on the day in a 23-7 San Francisco win over Houston on Jan. 2, 2022.

800.description: Tee Higgins got behind the defense off of play action here, pulling in this pass from Joe Burrow and carrying it inside the Kansas City 40-yard line for a gain of 44 yards and a first down. Higgins caught six passes for 103 yards in the game, a 27-24 Bengals win in overtime against Kansas City in the AFC Championship Game on Jan. 30, 2022.

892.description: Taylor Heinicke surveyed the field and didn't see an open receiver, so he took it himself to the outside. Winning the race to the edge, he dove to the end zone for the score. Heinicke completed 14-of-24 passes for 212 yards and two touchdowns in the game, along with eight rushes for 21 yards and another score in Washington's 43-21 loss to Buffalo on Sept. 26, 2021.

570.description: Braxton Berrios decided to bring it out from two yards deep in the end zone. It turned out to be the right decision. Emerging from a hole around the 30-yard line, he won the foot race to the end zone for six points to give New York the lead. In addition to his work on special teams, Berrios caught five passes for 37 yards and ran the ball once for three yards in the Jets' 26-21 win over Jacksonville on Dec. 26, 2021.

515.description: On one of the most improbable interceptions you'll ever see, this pass looked like it would almost certainly fall to the ground for an incompletion. But it somehow bounced off of Dallas Goedert's hands and then off the heel of his cleat and right into the arms of Landon Collins for the interception. Washington took over at the Philadelphia 26-yard line and would score seven plays later for the game's first points. Collins finished with six total tackles, plus this interception and a fumble recovery, in Washington's 27-17 loss to the Eagles on Dec. 21, 2021.

504.description: On a nicely placed ball just over the reach of the defender, Cooper Kupp reeled in this pass and took it across the goal line for the score. It was one of two touchdowns on the night for Kupp, who tallied 136 yards on nine catches in the Rams' 20-10 win over Seattle on Dec. 21, 2021.

1110.description: Wide receiver Tyler Boyd was throwing a pass instead of catching one here, rolling out to the right after taking a pitch back from quarterback Joe Burrow. That's when he spotted fellow receiver Ja'Marr Chase down the field, threading a pass between two Miami defenders for a gain of 23 yards and a first down. It was Boyd's lone pass attempt of the game. He also caught two passes for 47 yards, part of a 27-15 win over Miami on Sept. 29, 2022.

465.description: After a furious Pittsburgh comeback, Minnesota's defense had a chance to make one last stand and secure the victory. They did that on this last-second Steelers pass with 0:03 to play, as quarterback Ben Roethlisberger threaded the needle between three Vikings defenders, who converged to jar the ball loose. As it fell to the ground with zeroes on the clock, Minnesota celebrated its 36-28 win on Dec. 9, 2021.

819.description: Pressure around the edge forced Rams quarterback Matthew Stafford to step up into the pocket, where Cincinnati's D.J. Reader was waiting to take him down for the sack. It was Reader's lone tackle in the game and one of two sacks for the Bengals as a team in a 23-20 loss to Los Angeles in Super Bowl LVI on Feb. 13, 2022.

757.description: K'Waun Williams made this impressive interception as he was falling to the ground in the third quarter, giving the 49ers an instant offensive possession in Dallas territory after the turnover. Williams added two total tackles in San Francisco's 23-17 win over the Cowboys on Jan. 16, 2022.

635.description: George Kittle got one hand on this pass from Trey Lance, which was enough to get it under control and pull it into his body to secure the impressive catch. He picked up 29 yards on the play and a first down in Houston territory. It was Kittle's lone catch of the game in a 23-7 San Francisco win over the Texans on Jan. 2, 2022.

633.description: P.J. Williams deftly sidestepped a would-be blocker as he cut back inside on this play, giving him a clear path to the quarterback. The hit he delivered on Sam Darnold dislodged the football and sent it bouncing into the arms of teammate Marcus Davenport, who recovered to give the ball back to the New Orleans offense. Williams added three total tackles in an 18-10 victory over Carolina on Jan. 2, 2022.

394.description: Two shifty cuts and a broken tackle later, Cordarrelle Patterson was off and running into the red zone for a gain of 39 yards. He finished with 13 carries for 78 yards, with three catches for 18 yards in a 30-17 loss to Tampa Bay on Dec. 5, 2021.

908.description: Michael Gallup came across the formation as quarterback Dak Prescott scrambled away from pressure. With one step on a defender, he pulled in the pass from Prescott for the first down. Gallup caught five passes for 44 yards in the game, a 19-9 Dallas loss to Kansas City on Nov. 21, 2021.

822.description: Andrew Whitworth became just the eighth player in his 40s to play in the Super Bowl, anchoring the left side of the Los Angeles offensive line in his team's 23-20 victory over Cincinnati on Feb. 13, 2022. The Walter Payton Man of the Year award winner and his line allowed just two sacks in the game, keeping quarterback Matthew Stafford upright and helping him to throw for 283 yards and three touchdowns in the victory.

1188.description: Amon-Ra St. Brown was in the Thanksgiving spirit after this touchdown grab against Buffalo. Once he secured the one-yard score on a route toward the corner of the end zone, his teammates sat in front of them and waited for their 'meals', which St. Brown 'served' to each. St. Brown caught nine passes for 122 yards and a touchdown in the game, a 28-25 loss to the Bills on Thanksgiving Day, Nov. 24, 2022.

947.description: T.J. Hockenson caught this pass over the middle and turned it up the field, eyeing a defender near the 35-yard line. The tight end took the vertical route, hurdling the defender and setting Detroit up with a new set of downs out toward midfield after a gain of 24 yards. Hockenson caught six passes for 51 yards in the game, a 13-10 Lions loss to Cleveland on Nov. 21, 2021.

433.description: Backpedaling. Spinning. Breaking tackles. Javonte Williams did it all while keeping his balance to take this one in for the touchdown against Detroit. Williams carried the ball 15 times for 73 yards and had this catch for 10 yards to go along with two total touchdowns in Denver's 38-10 victory over Detroit on Dec. 12, 2021.

493.description: Between a pair of defenders and without much room to operate in the back of the end zone, Gabriel Davis pulled in this pass from Josh Allen and got both feet inbounds for the score. He caught five passes for 85 yards and two touchdowns in Buffalo's 31-14 win over Carolina on Dec. 19, 2021.

972.description: Jameis Winston kept his balance as a defender worked to pull him to the ground, just long enough to float this pass into the back of the end zone. In this jump ball situation, Marquez Callaway helped his quarterback, high-pointing the football and pulling it in for the seven-yard score. Winston completed 13-of-21 passes for 128 yards and two touchdowns in the game, a 28-13 New Orleans win over New England on Sept. 26, 2021.

1057.description: A diving interception by Jaire Alexander ended any Chicago hopes of a fourth-quarter comeback, as he tracked quarterback Justin Fields and laid out to pull in this pick and effectively end the game. Green Bay would drain the clock from there, putting a cap on its 27-10 victory over the Bears on Sept. 18, 2022. Alexander added three total tackles in the game.

501.description: Looking to add to their lead before the break, Josh Reynolds got good position on the defender on this post route and rose up to pull in the pass from Jared Goff and secure it for the 22-yard score. The ensuing extra point gave the Lions a 17-0 lead at the half and they would go on to win, 30-12, over Arizona on Dec. 19, 2021. Reynolds finished with six catches for 68 yards and this score.

653.description: Five Los Angeles defenders surrounded Noah Fant as he cut the ball up the field after making this reception in the third quarter, but he burst past the first-down marker, past midfield, and kept it moving into Chargers territory for a 35-yard gain. It was one of six catches on the day for Fant for 92 yards and a touchdown in Denver's 34-13 loss to Los Angeles on Jan. 2, 2022.

566.description: Clyde Edwards-Helaire pinballed his way into the end zone on this play, bouncing off a would-be Steelers tackle for a loss and breaking to the outside to stroll in for the score from one yard out. Edwards-Helaire carried the ball nine times for 27 yards and this touchdown in a 36-10 Kansas City win over Pittsburgh on Dec. 26, 2021.

815.description: DeVonta Smith got a step on his defender on the far sideline and Jalen Hurts floated this pass to him for the score, giving Smith his first career NFL catch and first career NFL touchdown. After an extra point, Philadelphia took a 7-3 lead in the first quarter over Atlanta and would never trail again in a 32-6 road victory on Sept. 12, 2021. Smith finished with six catches for 71 yards and a touchdown in the win.

589.description: Clinging to a four-point lead and with Detroit set up with a 1st and Goal with just over 0:30 to play, Foye Oluokun put a stop to the Lions' comeback attempt. He undercut this route over the middle of the field and picked it off, sealing the win for Atlanta, 20-16, on Dec. 26, 2021. Oluokon tallied 14 total tackles in the victory.

528.description: Trailing by nine points with under four minutes to play, the Buccaneers needed a big play. C.J. Gardner-Johnson made sure that didn't happen. He trailed the receiver and, as the pass arrived, snuck in front to make the interception. Gardner-Johnson added seven total tackles in New Orleans' 9-0 win over Tampa Bay on Dec. 19, 2021.

592.description: Maxx Crosby was lurking on this play, working his way through the line before wrapping up the quarterback for the sack. It was one of three tackles on the day for Crosby in the Raiders' 17-13 win over Denver on Dec. 26, 2021.

1235.description: Haason Reddick was disruptive all afternoon for the Eagles against Chicago. Coming off the edge, he tallied two sacks and a hurry that forced an incompletion, keeping quarterback Justin Fields uncomfortable in the pocket throughout the game. Reddick's effort helped Philadelphia to a 25-20 win over the Bears on Dec. 18, 2022.

818.description: Just after his team's offense scored a touchdown out of halftime, Chidobe Awuzie gave the Bengals the ball back again shortly after, picking off this tipped pass in Los Angeles territory. Cincinnati would put a field goal on the board to extend their lead to a touchdown, but would not score after that in a 23-20 loss to the Rams in Super Bowl LVI. Awuzie added five total tackles in the game.

463.description: Third down and three yards to go, Washington was looking to tie the game, down by a touchdown late in the fourth quarter. Dallas needed a big play, and Randy Gregory delivered, plowing through the offensive line and grabbing onto quarterback Kyle Allen as he stepped up in the pocket. Trying to get rid of it, Allen would fumble and Jayron Kearse would pick up the loose ball for the game-sealing turnover. Dallas would burn out the clock from there in a 27-20 win over Washington on Dec. 12, 2021.

983.description: Jalen Ramsey anticipated this reverse and stayed home, darting past a would-be blocker and pulling down Marcus Johnson for a seven-yard loss. Ramsey had three total tackles and an interception in the game, a 28-16 loss to Tennessee on Nov. 7, 2021.

1055.description: Rookie Cade York stepped up in a massive way for his team in his NFL debut. With just 0:08 to play and his team trailing by two points, York lined up for a 58-yard field goal for the win. His kick split the uprights, finishing off the day 4-for-4 on field goals and 2-for-2 on extra points, helping Cleveland secure a 26-24 over Carolina on Sept. 11, 2022.

1221.description: John Johnson III took advantage of an incredibly unusual bounce, grabbing the ball as it popped into the air from a diving receiver's grasp to make a remarkable sideline interception on the game's first play from scrimmage. Johnson III went on to add a tackle and pass deflection to the stat sheet in what became a 27-14 Cleveland win over Houston on Dec. 4, 2022.

426.description: Cam Newton saw the defender on the edge shade toward the running back on the read option, freeing him up to pull the ball back and bounce it to the outside, where he broke a tackle and pushed through another would-be tackler to bring it in for the touchdown. Newton was the Panthers' leading rusher on the day with 47 yards. He was also 15-of-23 for 178 yards and an interception in Carolina's 29-21 loss to Atlanta on Dec. 12, 2021.

837.description: Cris Carter had to make nearly a full extension to pull in this deep ball from Daunte Culpepper and he did, securing the pass and tumbling into the end zone for a 47-yard score. It was one of eight catches on the day for Carter for 111 yards and this score in Minnesota's 31-26 victory over Detroit on Oct. 14, 2001.

555.description: On the first play of the fourth quarter, Isaiah McKenzie leaped into the air to pull down this scrambling pass from Josh Allen for a 28-yard gain and the first down. McKenzie caught 11 passes for 125 yards and a touchdown on the day in Buffalo's 33-21 win over New England on Dec. 26, 2021.

1107.description: Just inside Cleveland territory in the fourth quarter, Tyler Allgeier took this handoff and bounced it to the outside, keeping his legs moving as a defender tried to bring him down and powering inside the 10-yard line for a gain of 42 yards. Allgeier carried the ball 10 times for 84 yards in the game, part of a 23-20 Atlanta victory over Cleveland on Oct. 2, 2022.

750.description: Trey Hendrickson came roaring around the edge on this sack and locked in on Derek Carr as he loaded up to throw, knocking the ball loose on impact and forcing a fumble. Teammate Larry Ogunjobi would scoop it up for the recovery to set Cincinnati up with a new set of downs in Las Vegas territory. It was Hendrickson's lone tackle of the game, but a hugely impactful one, in a 26-19 Cincinnati win over the Raiders on Jan. 15, 2022.

942.description: Stephon Gilmore delivered for the Panthers with under two minutes to play in the game and the Falcons driving in Carolina territory. The corner stepped in front of this Matt Ryan pass, intended for tight end Kyle Pitts, and picked it off, giving possession back to Carolina and maintaining the team's nine-point lead. Gilmore added two tackles in the game, a 19-13 Panthers win over Atlanta on Oct. 31, 2021.

503.description: Tyson Campbell jumped the route to make this interception and give Jacksonville the ball back deep in Houston territory. Campbell added four tackles in the Jaguars' 30-16 loss to the Texans on Dec. 19, 2021.

652.description: Dallas dug into its bag of tricks as it tried to make a comeback in the fourth quarter against Arizona, with Dak Prescott tossing this pass back to Cedrick Wilson Jr., who then looked back across the field to see Tony Pollard leaking out of the backfield. Pollard pulled in the pass for a 31-yard gain and a first down into Cardinals territory. It was Wilson Jr.'s lone pass on the day to go along with six catches for 35 yards and a touchdown in the Cowboys' 25-22 loss to Arizona on Jan. 2, 2022.

1225.description: With the Kansas City defense backed up against its own end zone on fourth down, Carlos Dunlap burst through the line to stop the Bengals' attempt at an end-around in its tracks for a three-yard loss. Dunlap had four tackles on the day, including that one for a loss, though the Chiefs fell 27-24 on Dec. 4, 2022.

513.description: T.J. Watt came around the edge and couldn't be stopped here en route to the quarterback. With this sack, his 17th of the season, Watt now holds Pittsburgh's single-season franchise record for sacks. Watt had five total tackles and 1.5 sacks in a 19-13 Steelers win over Tennessee on Dec. 19, 2021.

749.description: C.J. Uzomah sat down in the end zone on this route and made himself a target for quarterback Joe Burrow, who found him for the tight-window score. Uzomah celebrated with Cincinnati's favorite dance move to cap a 10-play, 75-yard drive that gave the Bengals an early 7-3 lead. They would never trail again in a 26-19 win over Las Vegas on Jan. 15, 2022. Uzomah finished with six catches for 64 yards and this score in the win.

844.description: Steve McNair dropped back to pass before deciding to do it himself, darting through the line and weaving his way through Baltimore's defense for a 15-yard touchdown. It was one of two rushing touchdowns on the day for McNair to go along with a 22-of-45 day passing for 219 yards. The Oilers would ultimately fall to the Ravens, 21-19, on Dec. 14, 1997.

568.description: Lil'Jordan Humphrey's back-shoulder adjustment was impressive enough. But, it was the ability to stay on his feet and recover for a gain of 56 yards that truly made this play special. The play flipped the field for New Orleans, setting them up in Miami territory after one play earlier being in the shadow of their own goal post. Humphrey had three catches for 70 yards on the night in a 20-3 loss to Miami on Dec. 27, 2021.

883.description: One big cutback, then another, was enough to spring James Robinson forward for a first down on this run. He carried the ball four times for 22 yards and caught one pass for 17 yards in the game, a 31-7 Jaguars loss to Seattle on Oct. 31, 2021.

564.description: T.Y. Hilton settled into a soft spot in the Arizona defense and the Colts took advantage, with Carson Wentz floating this pass to his wide receiver, then Hilton reeling it in and taking it into the red zone to set Indianapolis up with a fresh set of downs. Hilton caught four passes for 51 yards and a touchdown in the Colts' 22-16 win over Arizona on Dec. 25, 2021.

1160.description: Miami's creativity at the goal line got them six points here, with Alec Ingold coming in motion and taking the snap before sneaking it into the end zone for the score. It was his lone rush of the game, with that key one yard helping the Dolphins to a 31-27 road victory over Detroit on Oct. 30, 2022.

753.description: Matthew Stafford notched his first career playoff win in this victory over the Cardinals, going 13-of-17 passing for 202 yards with two touchdowns and no interceptions. He also carried the ball six times for 22 yards in Los Angeles' 34-11 victory over Arizona on Jan. 17, 2022.

565.description: This catch by Byron Pringle on the slant was just the start. After the grab, he stopped on a dime to shake off one defender, then dipped under another to free himself for the score. Pringle caught six passes for 75 yards and two touchdowns in Kansas City's 36-10 win over Pittsburgh on Dec. 26, 2021.

397.description: Darrel Williams saw his quarterback scrambling and found an opening down the field, where Patrick Mahomes II saw him and floated it to him for the first. Williams finished with three catches for 60 yards and five carries for 20 yards in the Chiefs' 22-9 victory on Dec. 5, 2021.

834.description: LeRoy Butler rushed around the edge, speeding by two would-be blockers to arrive at the quarterback and take him down for the sack. He tallied 1.5 sacks on the day in a 13-7 Green Bay win over Tampa Bay on Oct. 27, 1996.

374.description: As Matt Ryan looked to escape the pocket and buy more time, Ndamukong Suh was there to greet him with a sack. It was one of two sacks and four total tackles on the day for Suh in a 30-17 win over Atlanta on Dec. 5, 2021.

366.description: At first, Mack Hollins may not have secured this Tua Tagovailoa pass, but there was no panic. As he turned and began falling to the ground, he stayed focused, pulled it in, and dragged two feet inbounds for the score. This touchdown was his lone catch of the game in a 20-9 win over New York on Dec. 5, 2021.

781.description: Travis Kelce was matched up on a linebacker in the end zone here, adjusting perfectly to this back-shoulder pass from Patrick Mahomes II and tapping two feet inside the boundary to complete the catch. The score gave Kansas City a 42-36 overtime victory and earned them a spot in the AFC Championship Game. Kelce caught eight passes for 96 yards and this score in the win.

968.description: Jordan Love's first career NFL touchdown pass came as the Packers were looking to get back into the game with under five minutes to play against Kansas City. Love found wide receiver Allen Lazard on an out route toward the far sideline, and Lazard pulled it in before dodging a would-be tackler and taking it in for the touchdown. Love finished 19-of-34 for 190 yards and a touchdown in the game, a 13-7 loss to the Chiefs on Nov. 7, 2021.

1099.description: Kenny Pickett was inserted into the game under center for the Steelers to provide a spark and it was his work on the ground that did just that. He carried the ball six times for 15 yards, including two touchdowns down near the goal line, to go along with 10-of-13 passing for 120 yards. Pittsburgh would fall to New York, though, 24-20, on Oct. 2, 2022.

690.description: Jared Cook found room to operate in the Las Vegas defense and Justin Herbert delivered this pass into Raiders territory for the first down. But Cook wasn't done, rumbling ahead to the edge of the red zone. Cook caught four passes for 80 yards in the game, a 35-32 overtime loss to the Raiders on Jan. 9, 2022.

999.description: Rookie Davante Adams delivered when Green Bay needed it most in the Divisional round, trailing by eight points with under two minutes to play in the third quarter. Breaking toward the middle of the field on a slant, quarterback Aaron Rodgers found him and Adams took it from there. He juked past one defender and won the foot race to the end zone for the 46-yard score. Adams caught seven passes for 117 yards in the game, a 26-21 win over Dallas on Jan. 11, 2015.

846.description: Rookie quarterback Chris Miller dropped back to pass off the play action and eyed his receiver with a step on his defender down the near sideline. Miller let it fly, hitting him in stride for the 51-yard touchdown. An extra point would even the score, 10-10, in the second quarter. Miller finished 16-of-36 for 196 yards in the game, a 30-13 loss to Detroit on Dec. 27, 1987.

943.description: Myles Garrett topped his previous career high for sacks in a season when he registered this takedown of Baltimore's Lamar Jackson, giving him 14 sacks on the year. It helped to halt the Ravens' opening drive, which ended in a punt three plays later. Garrett tallied five total tackles in the game, a 16-10 Browns loss to Baltimore on Nov. 28, 2021.

1159.description: Even with the pass rush closing in and a defender getting a hand on the football, Malik Willis was able to sling this ball to wide receiver Robert Woods for a gain of 16 yards and a first down for the Titans. Willis was 6-of-10 in the game for 55 yards in the game, a 17-10 Tennessee victory over Houston on Oct. 30, 2022.

634.description: Trailing by nine points and facing a 4th and Goal, Boston Scott did what he had to do to get into the end zone. He took the toss to the right and was patient as his blocks developed, then went airborne to evade a diving defender and cross the goal line for six. He carried the ball 14 times for 47 yards and two touchdowns on the day to go along with four receptions for 39 yards in Philadelphia's 20-16 win over Washington on Jan. 2, 2022.

631.description: This pass ended up wide of the intended receiver and J.C. Jackson was there to pick it off for New England. The pick tied him for the most interceptions through four seasons by any player in NFL history. He added four tackles on the day in a 50-10 Patriots win over Jacksonville on Jan. 2, 2022.

1164.description: Rookie Tyquan Thornton had a breakout game against Cleveland, scoring his first two career NFL touchdowns -- one on the ground and one through the air. He caught four passes for 37 yards and carried the ball three times for 16 in the game, a 38-15 New England win over the Browns on Oct. 16, 2022.

388.description: Under a minute to play. On the road. Down by a point. Brian Johnson was clutch for Washington, knocking through this 45-yard field goal to give WFT the lead that would ultimately be the deciding margin, 17-15, on Dec. 5, 2021.

702.description: Bobby McCain saw exactly where this Jake Fromm pass was headed and jumped the route, picking the ball off and taking it back 30 yards for the touchdown to extend Washington's lead. It was one of two interceptions on the day for McCain in a 22-7 Washington win on Jan. 9, 2022.

632.description: Jakobi Meyers created separation as he broke toward the back corner of the end zone and quarterback Mac Jones put it in the perfect spot. As the defender closed the gap and pulled him down, Meyers maintained possession and completed the catch to extend New England's first-half lead. Meyers caught eight passes for 73 yards and this touchdown on the day in a 50-10 New England victory over the Jaguars on Jan. 2, 2022.

1149.description: Rookie Alec Pierce's first career NFL touchdown couldn't have come at a more important time for the Colts, who trailed by a point with just 0:23 to play. On the score, Pierce got separation and quarterback Matt Ryan found him down the near sideline, with the rookie pulling it in and taking it across the goal line to put Indianapolis in front. Pierce caught three passes for 49 yards and this score in the game, a 34-27 Colts victory over the Jaguars on Oct. 16, 2022.

802.description: Down by 10 late in the third quarter, the Rams reached into the play vault for a classic flea flicker. Tight end Kendall Blanton locked up with a defensive lineman at the snap of the ball, tossed him off-balanced, and slipped out of the chaos in the pocket to secure the pass in the flat with grass in front of him. He picked up 20 yards off the screen behind blocks from teammates Rob Havenstein and Brian Allen. Blanton would finish with 57 yards on five receptions in the 20-17 win over their divisional rival in the NFC Championship Game on Jan. 30, 2022.

622.description: Even three defenders couldn't stop AJ Dillon in his pursuit of the end zone here. Taking the handoff out of the shotgun, Dillon sliced through a hole and took on not one, not two, but three Vikings and stayed on his feet to push across the goal line for the score. Dillon carried the ball 14 times for 63 yards and two touchdowns in Green Bay's 37-10 win over Minnesota on Jan. 2, 2022.

373.description: When Russell Wilson throws it up in a tight window, he has confidence that wide receiver Tyler Lockett will come down with it. The duo tallied another touchdown here, one of two scores for Wilson on a 30-of-37, 231-yard passing day in a 30-23 win over San Francisco on Dec. 5, 2021.

621.description: Brandon McManus lined up for a 61-yard field goal with 0:02 to play before the half, looking to put the first Denver points on the board against Los Angeles. McManus made sure his team headed to the locker room with three points in their pocket, knocking through this long kick as time expired. He made both of his field goal attempts on the day, as well as his lone extra point attempt, in a 34-13 loss to the Chargers on Jan. 2, 2022.

685.description: D'Andre Swift saw no space in front of him, so he bounced it to the left and beat the Packers' defense to the edge to carry it in for a 14-yard touchdown. The score gave Detroit the lead with under two minutes to play in the fourth quarter and they would go on to win, 37-30, on Jan. 9, 2022. Swift finished with seven carries for 30 yards in the victory.

1155.description: Pittsburgh was driving, looking to take the lead in the fourth quarter. Jevon Holland would have none of that. He picked off this pass from Kenny Pickett in the red zone, halting a promising Steelers drive and returning it out toward midfield. Holland added five total tackles in the game, a 16-10 Miami win over Pittsburgh on Oct. 23, 2022.

1300.description: Luke Kuechly was in the right place at the right time to take advantage of this errant pass, which sailed wide of the intended target and into the arms of the star linebacker. But Kuechly wasn't done. He planted his foot and took off for the pylon on the near sideline, winning the race for the 14-yard touchdown. He added 11 total tackles in the game to help Carolina to a 31-24 victory over Seattle on Jan. 17, 2016.

1304.description: After missing the previous few weeks, Richard Seymour returned in a big way for the Patriots in Super Bowl XXXIX, helping to disrupt Eagles quarterback Donovan McNabb throughout the game and contributing one of the four sacks the New England defense totaled on the day. The Patriots would go on to win their third Super Bowl in four years, 24-21, over the Eagles on Feb. 6, 2005.

891.description: Derrick Henry caught this screen pass and looked up the field. Darius Leonard, in search of a turnover, tried to jar the ball loose, but Henry powered through to finish the run and pick up the first down. Henry caught three passes for 31 yards and carried the ball 28 times for 113 yards in the game, a 25-16 Titans win over Indianapolis on Sept. 26, 2021.

1105.description: Rookie Jack Jones shifted the momentum for the Patriots before halftime, intercepting quarterback Aaron Rodgers and taking it 40 yards to the house for six. That flipped a four-point deficit into a three-point halftime lead after the extra point. Jones also forced and recovered a fumble and tallied seven total tackles in the game, a 27-24 overtime loss to Green Bay on Oct. 2, 2022.

887.description: Kadarius Toney took the pitch and looked downfield for an open receiver, finding Sterling Shepard for the first down. It was the lone pass of the game for Toney for 19 yards. He also caught four passes for 26 yards in the game, a 20-17 New York loss to Kansas City on Nov. 1, 2021.

993.description: Larry Fitzgerald started his first-ever playoff game with some fireworks against Atlanta. In Falcons territory on the team's first drive of the game, Fitzgerald went deep on a designed flea flicker. The deep pass was in the air as two Atlanta defenders surrounded Fitzgerald and he made a full, leaping, backward extension to make the grab for the 42-yard touchdown. Fitzgerald finished with six catches for 101 yards and this score in Arizona's 30-24 win over the Falcons on Jan. 3, 2009.

467.description: Jostled loose. Up in the air. That's another turnover created by Tyrann Mathieu. It was one of five turnovers for the Kansas City defense, but the lone interception, in a 48-9 victory over Las Vegas on Dec. 12, 2021. Mathieu finished with five total tackles, a fumble recovery, and this interception on the day.

558.description: On third down and long, D'Ernest Johnson delivered this stick-moving run to the right side, cutting up the field and rumbling 30 yards down inside the Green Bay five-yard line. Cleveland would score on the next play to pull within two points but was ultimately unable to complete the comeback in a 24-22 loss to the Packers. Johnson carried the ball four times for 58 yards on the night.

361.description: From 56 yards out, Harrison Butker powered this one through the uprights, even after hitting the upright on the way in. Butker made all three of his field goal attempts and one of his two extra-point attempts in the Chiefs' 22-9 win over Denver on Dec. 5, 2021.

1094.description: Christian Watson's first career NFL touchdown put the Packers on the board against New England and he celebrated accordingly, leaping into the crowd at Lambeau Field as he took in the moment. It was his lone carry of the game and he also caught one pass for eight yards, part of a 27-24 overtime victory for Green Bay on Oct. 2, 2022.

682.description: A single-season franchise passing touchdown record and a career high? With this pass to Corey Clement in the flat, Dak Prescott achieved both. It was one of five touchdown passes on the day for Prescott, who finished 21-of-27 for 295 yards through the air, and the 37th score of the season through the air for the quarterback. Dallas would go on to win, 51-26, on Jan. 8, 2022.

700.description: Julio Jones' first touchdown as a Titan came in a big spot for Tennessee, looking to extend their lead midway through the fourth quarter in Houston. Coming off the line of scrimmage, he found a soft spot in the Texans' defense in the back of the end zone and pulled in this Ryan Tannehill pass for the score. Jones caught five passes for 58 yards and this score in a 28-25 Tennessee win over Houston on Jan. 9, 2022.

630.description: A'Shawn Robinson pushed his way through the line on this sack, freeing himself and bringing down quarterback Tyler Huntley for a loss of 11 yards. After the early setback because of the sack, Baltimore would go three and out on the drive. Robinson had six total tackles on the day in a 20-19 Rams win over the Ravens on Jan. 2, 2022.

629.description: Some patented Keenan Allen footwork was on display here, as he faked to the far sideline and broke back inside to create a window for Justin Herbert. The quarterback fired a pass, Allen pulled it in, and the Chargers put six more points on the board before halftime. Allen caught four passes for 44 yards and this score in Los Angeles' 34-13 victory over Denver on Jan. 2, 2022.

626.description: Demarcus Robinson stepped to the outside, then broke back inside on this deep route to create space for quarterback Patrick Mahomes II to find him on this 29-yard touchdown pass to give Kansas City its first points of the game. On the day, Robinson caught two passes for 33 yards in a 34-31 Chiefs loss to Cincinnati on Jan. 2, 2022.

854.description: Brian Urlacher was lurking as quarterback Daunte Culpepper let this pass go in the red zone. Urlacher stepped in front and picked it off, stifling Minnesota's drive and giving the ball back to Chicago's offense. Urlacher added eight total tackles and 1.5 sacks in the game, a 24-14 win over the Vikings on Dec. 5, 2004.

1236.description: On Dec. 11, 2022, Panthers wide receiver Terrace Marshall Jr. made one of the more unique and unlikely catches anyone will ever see. Crossing over the middle, Marshall somehow got his hands on a ball that split two defenders and then finished the catch by trapping the ball between his legs as he tumbled on the ground. It was his only catch on the day, but the Panthers went on to defeat the Seahawks, 30-24.

784.description: Trailing by seven points with no timeouts remaining and the Rams trying to run the clock out, Tampa Bay needed a turnover to keep its hopes alive. Ndamukong Suh delivered, getting his hand on the football as running back Cam Akers pushed for extra yards and forcing this fumble, which was recovered by the Buccaneers. Tampa Bay would score on the next drive to tie the game, though they would ultimately fall, 30-27, to Los Angeles on Jan. 23, 2022. Suh had six tackles, including half a sack, in the loss.

684.description: Amon-Ra St. Brown pulled in this pass and immediately absorbed a hit from a Green Bay defender, then stayed on his feet to keep it moving into Packers territory for a 28-yard gain. The Lions would score four plays later to take the lead and they would go on to win, 37-30, on Jan. 9, 2022. St. Brown finished with eight catches for 109 yards and a touchdown.

995.description: Michael Thomas found a soft spot in the Rams' defense and pulled in this pass, then slammed on the brakes as a help defender came over the top, allowing him to fly by and open up a lane to the end zone. Thomas then powered through a would-be tackler for the 21-yard score. He caught nine passes in the game for 108 yards and two touchdowns, part of a 49-21 New Orleans win over Los Angeles on Nov. 27, 2016.

424.description: Russell Gage faked to the inside and broke back out toward the outside, freeing himself to grab this deep pass from Matt Ryan in the first quarter for Atlanta. Diving to make the grab, the Falcons picked up 36 yards and a first down on the play. Gage finished with four catches for 64 yards in Atlanta's 29-21 win over Carolina on Dec. 12, 2021.

559.description: Jerry Jeudy found space in the Las Vegas defense as he streaked across the formation here, pulling in the pass and turning it up the field on the far sideline. He cut it back in Raiders territory for more yardage and, in all, a 40-yard catch and run. Jeudy caught three passes for 60 yards on the day in a 17-13 loss to Las Vegas on Dec. 26, 2021.

432.description: Sack. Tackle for loss. Pass deflection. Dre'Mont Jones did a little bit of everything on one drive in the third quarter to force a turnover on downs and give the ball back to the Denver offense. He finished the game with two sacks and three total tackles in the Broncos' 38-10 win over the Lions on Dec. 12, 2021.

496.description: Bouncing it to the outside, Chuba Hubbard found a lot of green space on this run. He picked up the first down and kept moving deeper into Buffalo territory, inside the 25-yard line. Hubbard finished with eight carries for 40 yards on the day in a 31-14 loss to Buffalo on Dec. 19, 2021.

967.description: David Montgomery eluded one defender, then pushed his way through a crowd of Lions en route to the end zone, carrying it nine yards for the touchdown. Montgomery had 23 carries for 106 yards and two scores in the game, a 24-14 victory over Detroit on Oct. 3, 2021.

561.description: With just over 0:30 to play in the first half, Davis Mills loaded up to get this ball deep down the far sideline to Chris Conley on the go route. Mills put it right on target and Conley pulled it in with the defender all over him for the score. Mills completed 21 of his 27 passes for 254 yards and two touchdowns on the day in a 41-29 win over the Chargers on Dec. 26, 2021.

1019.description: There wasn't a lot of space to fit the football into this window, but Aaron Rodgers did it with this touchdown pass against Detroit. Pinpointing it just over the defender's head, he hit tight end Robert Tonyan for the 22-yard score to give Green Bay a lead in the third quarter. Rodgers finished 22-of-27 for 255 yards and four touchdowns in the game, a 35-17 win over Detroit on Sept. 20, 2021.

654.description: Aaron Jones took this toss from Aaron Rodgers in the shotgun and found a hole to the left side, but it was the stiff-arm he dished out in the second level of the defense that really propelled him forward for a gain of 28 yards and a first down into Minnesota territory. Jones carried the ball eight times for 76 yards and caught five passes for 30 yards in Green Bay's 37-10 win over the Vikings on Jan. 2, 2022.

882.description: Courtland Sutton saw the defender breaking hard toward him in pursuit of the ball, so he simply took a step back, let the defender pass by, and pushed his way into the end zone for the score. Sutton caught eight passes for 94 yards and this touchdown in the game, a 34-24 Denver loss to Las Vegas on Oct. 17, 2021.

693.description: Ihmir Smith-Marsette was able to shake one defender in the middle of the field and pull this pass in before help arrived for this 44-yard score. Smith-Marsette caught three passes for 103 yards on the day in Minnesota's 31-17 victory over Chicago on Jan. 9, 2022.

699.description: Scott Miller took this pitch on the end-around and had blockers in front. He did the rest. Showing some patience and fancy footwork down near the goal line, Miller snuck this one in for the 33-yard score. He carried the ball twice for 43 yards and caught one pass for nine yards in a 41-17 Tampa Bay win over Carolina on Jan. 9, 2022.

1224.description: On the opening play of the second half of Indianapolis' Week 11 game with the Eagles, Yannick Ngakoue came flying around the edge and knocked the ball out of quarterback Jalen Hurts' hand to force the turnover. Ngakoue finished with 1.5 sacks on the game to go with that forced fumble, but the Colts ultimately fell to the Eagles 17-16 on Nov. 20, 2022.

395.description: On third down, the Cowboys needed seven yards. Amari Cooper reeled in this grab and got Dallas a lot more. The 41-yard grab was one of his two catches on the day in a 27-17 win over New Orleans on Dec. 2, 2021.

1303.description: With immortality on the line, Dolphins quarterback Bob Griese stepped back in the pocket and fired a precise pass downfield to receiver Howard Twilley, who hauled it in and fought for the final few yards to get the ball across the goal line and open the scoring in Super Bowl VII. Griese finished the day with 88 passing yards and the one score as he orchestrated the Dolphins to the tough 14-7 victory over Washington to finish off their perfect 17-0 season on Jan. 14, 1973.

687.description: Josiah Deguara slipped off of his block to give Jordan Love a target on this play, catching the screen and doing the rest himself. Slipping a tackle near the first-down marker, he crossed over midfield and outran the defense for a 62-yard touchdown. Deguara caught three passes for 66 yards and this score in Green Bay's 37-30 loss to Detroit on Jan. 9, 2022.

798.description: Joe Burrow was in the defender's grasp in the pocket on this critical third down in the fourth quarter, but refused to go down, wriggling away and rolling out toward the near sideline. He hurried past a Chris Jones dive and eyed the seven yards in front of him that he needed for the first. The possibility of a throw was just enough to freeze the defender in front of him and he scampered past the first-down marker to give Cincinnati a fresh set of downs. Burrow finished 23-of-38 for 250 yards with two touchdowns and one interception in the game and helped his team to a 27-24 overtime victory against the Chiefs in the AFC Championship Game on Jan. 30, 2022.

438.description: Route precision? That's Hunter Renfrow. Darting inside before breaking back toward the pylon on the right side, he shook the defender and quarterback Derek Carr found him for six points. Renfrow had 13 catches for 117 yards and this touchdown in a 48-9 loss to Kansas City on Dec. 12, 2021.

1044.description: Garrett Wilson's first career touchdown was all about footwork. A quick move to the inside and then back toward the corner of the end zone freed Wilson and allowed quarterback Joe Flacco to loft this ball to where only Wilson could get it. He pulled it in for the score to help tie the game in the second quarter against Cleveland. Wilson was impressive in his second career NFL game, catching eight passes for 102 yards and two touchdowns in New York's come-from-behind 31-30 win over the Browns on Sept. 18, 2022.

1000.description: Patrick Peterson fielded this punt on his own one-yard line in overtime against the Rams. What followed was magic. He found a hole and dodged a swarm of would-be St. Louis tacklers. It was a foot race from there that he would win, an unforgettable 99-yard return to give Arizona the win in the extra period. Peterson added three tackles and defended three passes in Arizona's 19-13 victory on Nov. 6, 2011.

507.description: Justin Jefferson's fake to the inside and move toward the back corner of the end zone created the space he needed to reel in this pass from quarterback Kirk Cousins for the touchdown. Jefferson caught four passes for 47 yards and this score in a 17-9 Vikings win over Chicago on Dec. 20, 2021.

1157.description: Javon Hargrave power through two would-be blockers on this play, arriving in the backfield and taking down quarterback Kenny Pickett for the sack. Hargrave tallied eight total tackles, including two sacks, in the game, part of a 35-13 Philadelphia victory over Pittsburgh on Oct. 30, 2022.

1232.description: Jonathan Jones took matters into his own hands to put the game firmly out of reach, intercepting a deflected pass just before it hit the turf, spinning away from one tackler, and then taking the ball into the end zone for the score. The touchdown put the Patriots ahead of the Colts 26-3, which is how the game would end. Jones totaled one tackle in addition to that pick-six in the matchup on Nov. 6, 2022.

444.description: Zach Wilson saw the field open up in front of him and didn't hesitate. Running for the first before sliding down in Saints territory, this 18-yard chunk play was New York's longest rush of the day. Wilson was 19-of-42 on the day through the air for 202 yards and carried the ball four times for 33 yards in the Jets' 30-9 loss to New Orleans on Dec. 12, 2021.

529.description: Baltimore went for it on 4th and Goal from inside the five-yard line and, despite scrambling to buy time, Green Bay's defense held up to get the stop and the turnover on downs. De'Vondre Campbell was in pursuit and forced quarterback Tyler Huntley toward the sideline before wrapping him up behind the line for the sack. Campbell finished with 10 total tackles in the game, a 31-30 Green Bay victory over Baltimore on Dec. 19, 2021.
