The trick play was made possible after the pitch to Mixon pulled the Los Angeles defense toward him, opening room for Higgins in the back of the end zone. It was Mixon's lone pass attempt of the game. He also carried the ball 15 times for 72 yards, though the Bengals would ultimately fall to the Rams in Super Bowl LVI, 23-20.

1043.description: Coming across the formation, Allen Robinson II was able to shake free from his defender, pull in this Matthew Stafford pass, and turn it up the field for the first down. Robinson caught four passes for 53 yards and a touchdown in the game, a 31-27 Los Angeles victory over Atlanta on Sept. 18, 2022.

934.description: Three defenders were in the area, waiting to intercept this Jalen Hurts pass, but wide receiver Jalen Reagor went up and pulled it in, then took it in for the 17-yard touchdown. Reagor caught two passes for 25 yards and this score in the game, a 33-22 Philadelphia loss to Las Vegas on Oct. 24, 2021.

1080.description: Breece Hall's first career NFL touchdown showed off the versatility that makes him such a multi-talented offensive player. Out of the shotgun, Hall was uncovered and pulled in this Joe Flacco pass, motoring across the goal line for the score before the defense could close the gap. He carried the ball seven times for 50 yards in the game to go along with this 10-yard score, helping to boost the Jets to a 31-30 come-from-behind victory over Cleveland on Sept. 18, 2022.

888.description: Elijah Moore came across the formation and took the toss on this play, looking down the field for space in the New England defense. He found a gap, darted through, and made his way 19 yards into the end zone for his first career NFL touchdown. Moore also caught one pass for 13 yards in New York's 54-13 loss to the Patriots on Oct. 24, 2021.

497.description: Coasting past a would-be blocker, Akiem Hicks was in the backfield just as the quarterback was trying to settle into the pocket, where he wrapped him up for the sack. Hicks had five total tackles, including two sacks, in Chicago's 17-9 loss to Minnesota on Dec. 20, 2021.

853.description: With the pass rush closing in, tied with the Jets in overtime, Byron Leftwich lofted this one up down the far sideline. Wide receiver Jimmy Smith created separation and pulled it in, absorbing contact and reaching the ball across the goal line for a 36-yard game-winning score. Leftwich finished 16-of-23 for 177 yards with two touchdowns in a 26-20 road victory for the Jaguars over New York on Sept. 25, 2005.

683.description: Facing a third down just outside the red zone, Drew Lock saw an opening and took advantage. A pair of drag routes pulled the defense toward the sidelines and Lock escaped the pocket up the middle. One cutback and a dive got Lock across the goal line for his second rushing touchdown of the game. Lock finished 12-of-24 passing for 162 yards and carried the ball four times for 35 yards and two scores in Denver's 28-24 loss to Kansas City on Jan. 8, 2022.

998.description: On the first play of Steve Smith Sr.'s career, he scored. The rookie received this opening kickoff in Week 1 against Minnesota, darted one way, weaved through a crowd of defenders, and was in the clear for a 93-yard touchdown. He also caught a pass for 16 yards in Carolina's 24-13 win over the Vikings on Sept. 9, 2001.

725.description: Devin Singletary needed two yards for the first down here and got plenty more. Emerging from a cloud of defenders at the line, Singletary picked up the first and shifted into another gear toward the near sideline. He would pick up 40 yards to give Buffalo a fresh set of downs inside the red zone. Singletary carried the ball 19 times for 88 yards and a rushing touchdown to go along with two catches for 24 yards and another score through the air in the Bills' 27-10 win over New York on Jan. 9, 2022.

782.description: Blanketed by a defender, running out of space along the sideline, and using just one hand, George Kittle somehow pulled in this pass and got to feet inbounds to complete the catch for the first down. Kittle caught four passes for 63 yards in the game, a 13-10 San Francisco win over Green Bay on Jan. 22, 2022.

574.description: Former track star Cyril Grayson got separation from his defender on this deep route down the far sideline and quarterback Tom Brady found him, dropping the pass to him in stride in Carolina territory. Grayson then brought it inside the 10-yard line to set Tampa up with a 1st and Goal after a 62-yard gain. Grayson caught three passes for 81 yards and carried the ball once for 14 yards in the Buccaneers' 32-6 win over Carolina on Dec. 26, 2021.

506.description: When Myles Gaskin disappeared into a cloud of linemen and defenders on this play, it seemed like the run had been stopped almost before it got started. But he emerged with a burst of speed, breaking a tackle in the second level of the defense and taking it for a 30-yard gain into Jets territory. Gaskin carried the ball 10 times for 54 yards in the Dolphins' 31-24 win over New York on Dec. 19, 2021.

1115.description: Jamal Agnew caught this pass in the flat and slammed on the brakes along the near sideline, shedding a would-be tackler and giving himself a path to the end zone. He powered through another Eagles defender and tumbled across the goal line for the four-yard score. Agnew caught four passes for 50 yards in the game, a 29-21 loss to Philadelphia on Oct. 2, 2022.

398.description: Some go around the defense. Some go through. Taysom Hill went over on this big gain into Cowboys territory on third down. It was the most eye-popping of Hill's 11 carries for 101 yards on the night, which came in a 27-17 loss to Dallas on Dec. 2, 2021.

1113.description: Clinging to a one-point lead with under two minutes to play, Denver's defense needed to make a stand and it did. P.J. Locke stripped Jeff Wilson Jr. after a short completion, with Kareem Jackson recovering the ball and ending San Francisco's hopes of a come-from-behind win. Denver would secure the victory, 11-10, on Sept. 25, 2022.

1145.description: Cole Kmet's first touchdown of the 2022 NFL season came off of play action, with the tight end drifting toward the back corner of the end zone before pulling in this Justin Fields pass for the score. Kmet caught two passes for 11 yards and this touchdown in the game, a 49-29 Chicago loss to Dallas on Oct. 30, 2022.

981.description: Washington trailed by two points with two minutes to play and aimed to get into field goal range for the win. They chipped away with the short passing game, working their way down to the Giants' 30-yard line with five seconds to play. The first attempt from kicker Dustin Hopkins was no good, but a New York penalty moved Washington up five yards and gave Hopkins a chance from 43 yards, which he took advantage of, knocking it through to give Washington a 30-29 victory on Sept. 16, 2021.

777.description: Joe Mixon saw congestion ahead of him on this run, so he cut it back to the far sideline and found a lot of open space. He added a bit of flair as he slipped past the goal line for the 16-yard score, extending Cincinnati's lead in the third quarter. Mixon carried the ball 14 times for 54 yards and this touchdown and caught six passes for 51 yards in the Bengals' 19-16 victory on Jan. 22, 2022.

511.description: Jalen Hurts rolled out to his right and fired this back-shoulder throw to Greg Ward Jr. for the score. It gave Philadelphia a 27-17 lead, the margin by which they'd go on to beat Washington, on Dec. 21, 2021. Hurts finished 20-of-26 for 296 yards with one touchdown and one interception in the victory.

1283.description: Adam Thielen became the fourth undrafted player in the Super Bowl era to reach 50 career touchdowns with this score. Coming off the line, he snuck through the Detroit defense and used some nifty footwork in the back of the end zone to stay inbounds for the score. Thielen caught six passes for 61 yards and this touchdown in the game, a 28-24 win over Detroit on Sept. 25, 2022.

816.description: Najee Harris eluded a would-be tackler after pulling in this short pass and that's where the fun really began. Racing toward the end zone as two defenders closed in, he launched into the air from three yards out and extended the ball past the goal line for the score. It was his first career NFL touchdown, part of a game where he tallied 38 yards on 10 carries and caught five passes for 43 yards. The Steelers would fall to Las Vegas, though, 26-17, on Sept. 19, 2021.

997.description: This pass was sinking fast as Keyshawn Johnson slid toward the near sideline to try to make the catch. He did, gripping the ball with his fingertips and keeping it off the turf to complete the 21-yard pass. Johnson caught four passes for 59 yards in the game, a 26-14 Tampa Bay victory over St. Louis on Sept. 23, 2002.

1305.description: Kam Chancellor took advantage of this overthrown pass forced by the Seahawks' pass rush, intercepting Broncos quarterback Peyton Manning late in the first quarter of Super Bowl XLVIII to set Seattle up with a chance to extend their early lead. Chancellor's big day included 10 tackles and two passes defended in addition to this interception, and the Seahawks rolled to a 43-8 win over Denver to claim the franchise's first Super Bowl title on Feb. 2, 2014.

1056.description: Coming off the bench because of an injury to starter Dak Prescott, Cooper Rush played the hero role for Dallas. He led a 6-play, 33-yard drive with under a minute to play in a tie game, getting the Cowboys into field goal range. Kicker Brett Maher hit from 50 yards out as time expired and Dallas notched the win, 20-17, on Sept. 18, 2022.

1163.description: It was the ground game where Kirk Cousins made an impact here, escaping the collapsing pocket before getting to the edge and diving into the end zone for a 17-yard score. Cousins carried the ball four times for 22 yards and this score, along with finishing 24-of-36 for 232 yards through the air with two more touchdowns. His effort helped Minnesota to a 34-26 win over Arizona on Oct. 30, 2022.

556.description: Khalil Herbert took the handoff out of the shotgun and found room to the left, cutting through the hole and bursting across the goal line for the 20-yard score. Herbert carried the ball twice for 21 yards on the day and caught one pass for seven yards in Chicago's 25-24 victory over Seattle on Dec. 26, 2021.

512.description: At first, blitzing the quarterback on 3rd and 3, Joe Schobert saw the ball had been tipped at the line. He raced underneath it, pulled it in, and took it back the other direction to set Pittsburgh's offense up in Tennessee territory. Schobert had seven total tackles in the Steelers' 19-13 win over the Titans on Dec. 19, 2021.

849.description: Matt Hasselbeck's first career touchdown pass came when he lined up as the holder on this Green Bay field goal attempt early in the fourth quarter against Minnesota. Down by four points, the Packers ran a fake, with Jeff Thomason leaking out to the left side and Hasselbeck finding him for the nine-yard score. It was his lone pass attempt of the game in a 24-20 Green Bay loss to the Vikings on Dec. 20, 1999.

354.description: Mark Andrews found a gap in the Pittsburgh defense and quarterback Lamar Jackson found Andrews to move the Baltimore offense inside the Pittsburgh 10-yard line. Andrews had four catches for 50 yards in his team's 20-19 loss to the Steelers on Dec. 5, 2021.

1050.description: Julian Love came on the blitz and got what he was after -- a sack on the quarterback. The third down takedown forced Carolina to punt while trailing by three with under three minutes to play in the fourth quarter. They would never get the ball back, as New York's offense ran out the clock and secured the win, 19-16, on Sept. 18, 2022. Love had eight total tackles in the victory.

1048.description: Derwin James Jr. would not let Travis Kelce into the end zone here. Planting his feet as Kelce looked to score, James lifted the tight end off the ground on this momentum-stopping tackle before taking him down almost on the spot. The drive would result in only a field goal for his efforts. He finished in nine total tackles in the Chargers' 27-24 loss to Kansas City on Sept. 15, 2022.

624.description: The defender arrived just as the ball did and somehow Marvin Jones Jr. was still able to pull in this grab for a gain of 22 yards. It was one of two catches for him on the day for 46 yards in a 50-10 loss to New England on Jan. 2, 2022.

443.description: Working against his defender near the sideline, Keelan Cole made a nice adjustment on this back-shoulder pass from Zach Wilson to pull it in for the first down. It was his lone catch of the game in New York's 30-9 loss to New Orleans on Dec. 12, 2021.

1108.description: What will go down in the box score as just a Baltimore first down was actually far from routine. First, quarterback Lamar Jackson escaped what looked like a sure sack. Then, Mark Andrews rose up over a defender as he tried to make the catch, but the pass bounced up in the air, looking like it was bound to fall incomplete or even be intercepted. But there was wide receiver Devin Duvernay, pulling it in and getting two feet down inbounds to make the catch and give the Ravens a new set of downs in Buffalo territory. The Ravens would finish the drive with a field goal but go on to fall, 23-20, to the Bills on Oct. 2, 2022.

688.description: Melvin Ingram shuffled past a would-be blocker and announced his presence in the backfield with this hit on running back Melvin Gordon III. He wrapped him up and brought him down for a loss of three yards. Ingram registered four tackles on the day in Kansas City's 28-24 win over Denver on Jan. 8, 2021.

848.description: Coming into the game for Green Bay's injured starter, second-year quarterback Brett Favre and the Packers had pulled within three in the fourth quarter against Cincinnati. With just 0:19 to play, Favre dropped back to pass, pump-faked, and launched this one deep down the far sideline. Wide receiver Kitrick Taylor had gotten a step on his defender and pulled it in for six. An extra point would give the Packers the lead and the win, 24-23. Favre finished 22-of-39 for 289 yards and two touchdowns in the victory on Sept. 20, 1992.

756.description: Likely his last touchdown pass in an NFL game, Ben Roethlisberger floated this one up to James Washington and the receiver went up and got it, pulling it in, tapping two feet inside the boundary, and completing the catch for the score. Roethlisberger completed 29-of-44 passes for 215 yards and two touchdowns in the game, a 42-21 loss to Kansas City that eliminated Pittsburgh from the playoffs on Jan. 16, 2022.

423.description: Christian Kirk got just a step on his defender as he worked back toward the near sideline on this deep ball and that was enough space to reel in the pass from Kyler Murray for a 41-yard gain. Kirk caught three passes on the night for 86 yards in a 30-23 loss to Los Angeles on Dec. 13, 2021.

801.description: Patrick Mahomes II didn't see anyone open as he dropped back to pass on this 1st and Goal, but stayed patient. Rolling out to his right, he eyed Tyreek Hill streaking toward the back corner of the end zone and fired this pass to the receiver, who pulled it in, tapped two feet, and completed the catch for the score, giving the Chiefs an early lead over the Bengals in the AFC Championship Game. Hill caught seven passes for 78 yards and this touchdown in the game, but his team would ultimately fall to Cincinnati, 27-24, in overtime on Jan. 30, 2022.
